Drop cuda.txt deps that are not packaged in nixpkgs and that vLLM either
imports lazily with a fallback or does not need on Lorian's Qwen3.6 NVFP4 path:

  - tilelang: only used by DeepSeek V4 / MHC paths that probe availability
    through vllm.utils.import_utils.has_tilelang().
  - fastsafetensors: weight_utils.py wraps the import in try/except and
    substitutes a PlaceholderModule on ImportError.
  - nvidia-cutlass-dsl + quack-kernels: Python packages for CuteDSL kernels
    that are not packaged in nixpkgs. The sm_120 build uses vLLM's
    vendored/source CUTLASS and QuTLASS paths.
  - tokenspeed-mla: faster MLA with spec decode; not on Qwen3.6 GDN/full-attn.
  - humming-kernels: optional mixed-precision quantization backend.

flashinfer-cubin and nvidia-cudnn-frontend stay in cuda.txt — both are
covered by `pythonRemoveDeps` in the package definition. flashinfer-python
stays too; `pythonRelaxDeps = true` lets us continue using nixpkgs'
flashinfer package even when its version lags upstream's strict pin.

diff --git a/requirements/cuda.txt b/requirements/cuda.txt
--- a/requirements/cuda.txt
+++ b/requirements/cuda.txt
@@ -12,18 +12,5 @@ torchvision==0.26.0 # Required for phi3v processor. See https://github.com/pytor
 flashinfer-python==0.6.12
 flashinfer-cubin==0.6.12
 apache-tvm-ffi==0.1.9
-tilelang==0.1.9
 nvidia-cudnn-frontend>=1.19.1
 
-# Required for faster safetensors model loading
-fastsafetensors >= 0.3.2
-
-# QuACK and Cutlass DSL for FA4 (cute-DSL implementation)
-nvidia-cutlass-dsl[cu13]==4.5.2
-quack-kernels>=0.3.3
-
-# Tokenspeed_MLA for faster mla with spec decode
-tokenspeed-mla==0.1.2
-
-# Humming kernels for quantization gemm
-humming-kernels[cu13]==0.1.4
